### [ 40. Nosferatu](https://www.timeout.com/movies/nosferatu-review-2025)
  * Film
  * Horror
  * Recommended


[![Nosferatu](https://media.timeout.com/images/106208096/750/422/image.jpg) ![Nosferatu](https://media.timeout.com/images/106208096/750/562/image.jpg) Foto: Focus Features](https://www.timeout.com/movies/nosferatu-review-2025)
Robert EggersŌĆÖ world-building breathes (or rather, bites) new life into one of the oldest tales in the horror canon. While faithful to FW MurnauŌĆÖs original 1922 Dracula riff, the production design puts the ŌĆśgrandŌĆÖ in Grand Guignol, masterfully using light, shadow and jaw-dropping set pieces to pull audiences under its spell. Speaking of trancelike states, Lily-Rose Depp delivers a remarkably physical performance as a possessed woman torn between her husband and her psychic demon lover. And though thereŌĆÖs no usurping Max Shreck for creepiness, Bill Skarsg├źrdŌĆÖs mustachioed Count Orlok is at once the most human and most repulsive the character has ever looked.
