### [ 39. Presence](https://www.timeout.com/movies/presence-review-2024)
  * Film
  * Horror
  * Recommended


[![Presence](https://media.timeout.com/images/106207896/750/422/image.jpg) ![Presence](https://media.timeout.com/images/106207896/750/562/image.jpg) Photograph: Neon](https://www.timeout.com/movies/presence-review-2024)
Steven Soderbergh fails at retirement once again, returning as his own cinematographer, cameraman and ŌĆō sort of ŌĆō lead actor in this haunted house story told from the ghostŌĆÖs point of view. This silent presence watches a new family move in, led by Lucy LiuŌĆÖs hard-charging mother, and sees a drama play around daughter Chloe (Callina Liang). ItŌĆÖs not about scaring so much as witnessing, but it makes for an effective twist on the ghost story.
