###  37. Pavements
![Pavements](https://media.timeout.com/images/106318262/750/422/image.jpg)
![Pavements](https://media.timeout.com/images/106318262/750/562/image.jpg)
"Pavements"
A fake biopic and a semi-real jukebox musical walk into a rock doc, and well, thatŌĆÖs the whole joke, which is appropriate for a movie about ŌĆÖ90s slacker heroes Pavement. As a band that never took itself very seriously, director Alex Ross PerryŌĆÖs half-sincere, half-ironic approach, featuring a collage of staged events alongside genuine footage, gets closer to articulating the groupŌĆÖs whole deal than an assemblage of talking heads ever could. The uninitiated still arenŌĆÖt likely to get it. But then, when it comes to Pavement, what else is new?
[![Matthew Singer](https://media.timeout.com/images/105942110/170/170/image.jpg)](https://www.timeout.com/profile/matthew-singer)
[Matthew Singer](https://www.timeout.com/profile/matthew-singer) Film writer and editor
