###  36. Eephus
![Eephus](https://media.timeout.com/images/106313636/750/422/image.jpg)
![Eephus](https://media.timeout.com/images/106313636/750/562/image.jpg)
Image: Neon
Comedian Hannibal Buress once joked that a baseball game is great if you need a quiet place to catch up with someone you havenŌĆÖt seen in years. Filmmaker Carson Lund might agree: his directorial debut is a tribute to AmericaŌĆÖs slow-moving pastime, but the focus is on the conversations that happen during the _many_ lulls in the action. A quintessential hangout movie, it watches as a group of middle-aged weekend warriors in small-town Massachusetts play their final innings at their home field before itŌĆÖs converted into a school. Wistful and funny, itŌĆÖs as much about the erosion of the so-called ŌĆśthird placeŌĆÖ as the game itself. But baseball proves an especially apt metaphor for the passage of time: most often, eras end not with a grand slam but with a walk.
