### [ 35. 28 Years Later](https://www.timeout.com/movies/28-years-later-review-2025)
  * Film
  * Horror


[![28 Years Later](https://media.timeout.com/images/106287557/750/422/image.jpg) ![28 Years Later](https://media.timeout.com/images/106287557/750/562/image.jpg) Photograph: Miya Mizuno/Sony Pictures](https://www.timeout.com/movies/28-years-later-review-2025)
In 2002, Danny BoyleŌĆÖs _28 Days Later_ single-handedly ushered in a golden age of the undead ŌĆō one thatŌĆÖs still going strong today. So returning to the series after 23 years came with high expectations. Working with original screenwriter Alex Garland, BoyleŌĆÖs blood-drenched sequel resists all the easy genre clich├®s, instead asking big questions about decaying society and focusing on a humble, heartfelt relationship. At its core, _28 Years Later_ is a moving coming-of-age story about the bond between a boy (superb newcomer Alfie Williams) and his mum (Jodie Comer), whose life is hard enough even without raging cannibals. ItŌĆÖs moving and, of course, very, very scary. A great start to a potential trilogy.
