### [ 34. F1: The Movie](https://www.timeout.com/movies/f1-review-2025)
  * Film
  * Action and adventure
  * Recommended


[![F1: The Movie](https://media.timeout.com/images/106288815/750/422/image.jpg) ![F1: The Movie](https://media.timeout.com/images/106288815/750/562/image.jpg) Photograph: Scott Garfield / Warner Bros. Pictures / Apple Original Films](https://www.timeout.com/movies/f1-review-2025)
An underdog racing drama turns to sports movie gold on the back of Brad PittŌĆÖs star power and the clean lines of Joseph KosinskiŌĆÖs hyper-stylish filmmaking. PittŌĆÖs veteran driver, ŌĆŗan old pro with a reckless streak the length of the N├╝rburgring, is obviously going to do Top Gun Maverick things ŌĆŗat some stage, but F1 ŌĆŗalways earns its big hero moments. The races are exhilarating, Damson Idris brings extra charisma as the insecure prot├®g├®, and Doja Cat spearheads a proper Bruckheimer blockbuster soundtrack.
