### [ 32. Memoir of a Snail](https://www.timeout.com/movies/memoir-of-a-snail-review-2025)
  * Film
  * Animation
  * Recommended


[![Memoir of a Snail](https://media.timeout.com/images/106232069/750/422/image.jpg) ![Memoir of a Snail](https://media.timeout.com/images/106232069/750/562/image.jpg) Photograph: Modern Films](https://www.timeout.com/movies/memoir-of-a-snail-review-2025)
WeŌĆÖre happy to report that Aussie animation wizard Adam Elliot has finally followed up 2009ŌĆÖs _Mary and Max_ with another sallow-eyed stop-motion yarn. This one, a more-than-slightly autobiographical story of a kid who wants to make stop-motion animations that look a lot like _Memoir of a Snail,_ is full of the pains and sorrows of growing up neglected and downtrodden in 1970s Melbourne. But ElliotŌĆÖs greatest skill, apart from crafting a world gnarled with a sense of the macabre, is sweetening the morbidness with dark wit, heart and hopefulness. The result is like Aardman for weirdos ŌĆō in the best way possible.
