###  30. Splitsville
![Splitsville](https://media.timeout.com/images/106317780/750/422/image.jpg)
![Splitsville](https://media.timeout.com/images/106317780/750/562/image.jpg)
Image: Neon
Co-stars Kyle Marvin and Michael Angelo Covino wrote this Apatowian farce about two longtime friends who decide to open their respective marriages, with disastrous consequences. (They also cast Dakota Johnson and Aria Arjona as their wives and, well, who among us?) Like many comedies about ŌĆśalternative relationshipsŌĆÖ, the movie ends up making a conservative argument in favor of traditional monogamy. Unlike many of them, itŌĆÖs funny as hell, with jokes flying from all angles, and a fight scene that finds the precise midpoint between [_They Live_](https://www.timeout.com/movies/they-live) and [_Pineapple Express_](https://www.timeout.com/movies/pineapple-express) _._
