From the makers of Nick Cave concept film _20,000 Days on Earth_ comes a kind of extended music video for a 2024 concept album by Icelandic singer-songwriter Emil├Łana Torrini. The music was inspired by a collection of love letters discovered after the eponymous Miss FlowerŌĆÖs death, and this film combines performances of the music with heartfelt readings, interpretive dance, acted vignettes and multimedia flights of fancy. Guided by artists utterly in command of their concept, Torrini and her collaborators ŌĆō including Cave, Alice Lowe and Richard Ayoade ŌĆō turn this recipe for pretentious pudding into an exquisitely intimate yet cinematic feast for the senses.
