Scandinavian director Joachim Trier is an empathetic observer of flawed humanity, and there are plenty of flaws to go around in this gently moving family drama. Stellan Skarsg├źrd is both charming and infuriating as an absentee filmmaker father whose only means of communicating with his children is through his art. A true actorŌĆÖs film, it features several of the yearŌĆÖs best performances, including Renate Reinsve as Skarsg├źrdŌĆÖs emotionally paralysed actress daughter and Elle Fanning as the movie star he tries to mold into her surrogate. Best among them might be the unheralded Inga Ibsdotter Lilleaas as the younger daughter caught in between them all, while nursing childhood wounds of her own.
