[![It Was Just An Accident](https://media.timeout.com/images/106277503/750/422/image.jpg) ![It Was Just An Accident](https://media.timeout.com/images/106277503/750/562/image.jpg) Photograph: Cannes Film Festival](https://www.timeout.com/movies/a-simple-accident-review-2025)
Drawn partly from his own persecution at the hands of the Islamic Republic, Iranian filmmaker Jafar PanahiŌĆÖs Palme dŌĆÖOr winner is his version of a genre movie, a revenge thriller filtered through _Waiting for Godot_. A onetime political prisoner (Vahid Mobasseri, somehow a first-time actor) kidnaps the guard he believes tortured him for months with the intent of burying him in the desert, only to be struck by a tinge of doubt that heŌĆÖs got the right guy. Intense stuff, but funny, too, as the cast grows into an ensemble of ex-prisoners arguing over what to do with whoever it is heŌĆÖs got locked in a trunk in the back of his transit van. The denouement, however, will have you holding your breath all the way to the parking lot.
