A big-budget gangster vampire blues musical period piece? In this economy? Writer-director Ryan Coogler reinvigorated the MCU and the _Rocky_ franchise, and he shoots much-needed adrenaline into blockbuster filmmaking in general here. Michael B Jordan plays twins, hustlers returning to the 1930s Mississippi Delta to open a juke joint and facing Klansmen by day and banjo-strumming bloodsuckers by night. An excellent ensemble cast, including Delroy Lindo and newcomer Miles Catron, carry the ŌĆśsurvive the nightŌĆÖ narrative, but itŌĆÖs CooglerŌĆÖs bold vision that makes the film a true event ŌĆō particularly the big-swing mid-movie music sequence thatŌĆÖll have folks talking for years.
