Fun as it was, Ryan CreggerŌĆÖs breakthrough horror [_Barbarian_](https://www.timeout.com/movies/barbarian-2022) was only the warm-up act for this masterful small-town fable, a horror-mystery that offers a _Pulp Fiction_ -like collage of perspectives and themes (alcoholism, dodgy policing, high-school shootings, social schisms) to complement its shocks and deeply satisfying freaky side. Julia Garner is a harried teacher who gets the blame when 17 classmates go missing one night. Only this puzzle has many more pieces than Josh BrolinŌĆÖs angry dad is prepared to accept. A genius, madcap final act brings it all together in memorable fashion. 
