Who needs dialogue? Gints Zilbalodis doesnŌĆÖt. The Latvian animation wizard piloted this spellbinding survival epic from his laptop all the way to the Oscars ŌĆō and all without a word of the stuff. Unless, that is, you count the odd ŌĆśmiaowŌĆÖ emanating from the inquisitive cat that it follows through a giant flood in the company of a ring-tailed lemur, a Labrador, a secretary bird and a capybara. Mystery, spirituality and plain old big-screen magic flow through a universally resonant tale of friendship and teamwork thatŌĆÖs worthy of Studio Ghibli.
