Did you know that Fidel Castro was a _Jaws_ fan? Or that the famously tumultuous shoot for Steven SpielbergŌĆÖs breakthrough blockbuster was once nearly interrupted by an _actual_ Great White. This rollickingly entertaining doc assembles filmmakers, fans, oceanographers and the odd Massachusetts local to find tell the tales of one of ŌĆÖ70s cinemaŌĆÖs most enduring classics. What emerges is a vivid depiction of PTSD, not just for shark-hunters Quint, Brody and Hooper, but a bright-eyed movie savant still haunted by nightmares of a broken mechanical shark 50 years on.
