The [first _Knives Out_ movie](https://www.timeout.com/movies/knives-out) was an amusing Agatha Christie throwback, and [the second](https://www.timeout.com/movies/glass-onion-a-knives-out-mystery-2022) a too-cute skewering of our current techbro-cracy. The third film, again directed by Rian Johnson, is easily the best so far, a surprisingly thoughtful murder mystery underpinned by themes of faith, forgiveness and Josh BrolinŌĆÖs masturbatory habits. Daniel Craig, sporting newly shaggy hair and the same Foghorn Leghorn accent, returns to investigate the death of a controversial preacher (Brolin) in upstate New York. But the movie truly belongs to Josh OŌĆÖConnor, whose soulful performance as a tortured boxer-turned-priest keeps the film grounded, even as it builds to the seriesŌĆÖ most convoluted whodunit yet. 
